commit_list.message:
(crudely) working shell

Takes in command from stdin and does a fork/exec of
the command. At the moment, no parsing of the commandline
is done, so only commands within the default system path
with no arguments will run successfully.

Also, none of the typical builtins for the shell are
implemented yet, e.g. `cd`

commit_list.message:
Add basic insert and select for "User" table

This is *really* crude. To wit:

* statements are *not* SQL
* statements are space-delimited, need to be in the right order
* statements have to explicitly include an id. No uniqueness enforcement
* Schema is explicitly hard-coded into definition of db
* Table is defined as an array of slabs in-memory

Add trivial ability to prepare and execute SQL statements

Only recognizes “select” and “insert”, and only in the lowercase.
Execution consists of recognizing the type of statement that’s been
prepared and stating as much

Extract meta command checking to separate function

This will make it easier to add  meta commands later on

Allow admin to edit Member without supplying user's password

See:
https://github.com/sferik/rails_admin/issues/2265#issuecomment-102791278

Prior to this change, verifying a member failed due to password
constraints on the underlying model.

This change adds rails_admin  configuration to prevent password fields
from being considered for editing. Additionally, this changes the admin
console to allow an admin to reset a member’s password via the
administrative interface.
